\n<Rui>...Something is peeling away. Something that has

\n<Yuuki>This is bad... I used to be able to interfere from

\n<Yuuki>I thought I'd get a reward if I could train you

\n<Yuuki>Yeah, it's impossible. So I'll leave it to the

\n<Yuuki>Welcome to Mad School! This is a labyrinthine
school building where villains who toy with girls

\n<Yuuki>The clear condition is simple. \C[4]【Escape from

\n<Yuuki>Of course, it's not a straightforward school

\n<Yuuki>A mad maze filled with villains who capture and
ravage lost girls... I wonder if you can escape!?

\n<Yuuki>That's all for the explanation. Thank you for

\n<Yuuki>Well, if you get caught by a man, you can just

\n<Yuuki>Indeed. It's a place designed to break captured

\n<Rui>At least the goal is clear. I'll clear it quickly.

\n<Yuuki>Right. Feel free. The next stage is through the

\n<Rui>...What should I do about my clothes?

\n<Yuuki>Give up. There's no way they're coming back after
you took them off in a place like this.

\n<Yuuki>Besides, running away while holding your arms like
that is going to be quite a burden, don't you
think? Well, if you want to be caught on purpose,
I don't mind.

\n<Rui>Can I ask just one last thing?

\n<Rui>Is it true that if we break that spell, the
eyeball will die?
\n<Yuuki>It's never been broken before, so I don't know.
\n<Rui>Now that you mention it, that makes sense...

\n<Yuuki>With a spell as outrageous as this one, there's no
way it would end without consequences.

\n<Yuuki>Besides, even if it's a lie, you, having been
freed, should be able to do something about it
with your power, right?

\n<Rui>I see... It's probably better to assume it's a
lie.

\n<Yuuki>Hehe, just kidding. In my opinion, there's zero

\n<Yuuki>Well, there is a possibility that the person

worse than death might be waiting.

\n<Yuuki>They don't have the guts to deceive someone
outright.

\n<Yuuki>Even after becoming such a grotesque form, they're
still just a child at heart. Fufu... Isn't that
cute?
\n<Rui>Could it be that you like them?
\n<Yuuki>I do like them. Is that a problem?

\n<Rui>...That's not what I meant! What I wanted to ask

\n<Yuuki>Ah, but the people captured in this world are all

\n<Yuuki>That's a lie. Well, there are some who might as

\n<Rui>Why would they tell such a pointless lie...

\n<Yuuki>Well... it's just a guess, but maybe someone's

\n<Yuuki>Despite having carefully planned everything, they

right... isn't that cute?

\n<Yuuki>Anyway, innocent girls are being violated and

\n<Rui>Yes, that's an important point. Thank you for

\n<Yuuki>Mhm mhm, glad to see you're motivated. Now off you

\n<Yuuki>...Wasn't there just one last thing you wanted to
ask?

\n<Rui>Are you by any chance one of the women captured by
the eyeball?

\n<Rui>Well, it's not about what... If you can be saved

\n<Yuuki>But men are different! With that attitude, you'll

\n<Yuuki>Remember this. A good woman isn't just cute,

\n<Yuuki>...You've had enough, right? Go on, get going.
\n<Yuuki>You there. Come here for a second.

An eternal corridor that tricks the mind into

Laying out these scenes, what kind of situation,

A lonely boy who can't return home, standing

Yes, ah, I see, I understand. Such fantasies are

Mutual justification among sinners. The pain-in-
the-ass woman is me.

Just a little bit. Yes, honestly, I can't say I
don't think about it.
